oc:kn_0004ac79 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building comparative analysis slides" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Comparative Analysis:
| Dimension | Company A | Company B | Company C |
|---|---|---|---|
| Scale | ●●● $160B | ●●○ $45B | ●○○ $8B |
| Growth | ●●○ +26% | ●●● +35% | ●●○ +22% |
| Margins | ●●○ 7.5% | ●○○ 3.2% | ●●● 15% |""" .

oc:kn_047d64ec a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the synthesis slide" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Moat Assessment:
| Moat | What to assess |
|---|---|
| Network effects | User/supplier flywheel strength; cross-side vs same-side |
| Switching costs | Technical integration depth, contractual lock-in, behavioral habits |
| Scale economies | Unit cost advantages at volume; minimum efficient scale |
| Intangible assets | Brand, proprietary data, regulatory licenses, patents |""" .

oc:kn_29143806 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extracting data from uploaded Excel/CSV files" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use source-file values exactly as given — do not recalculate or re-round. Same metric must show same value on every slide it appears. Same decimal precision as the source." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Recalculating user-provided data introduces discrepancies that erode trust in the analysis." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_2b0e559e a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Data comparability across competitors" ;
    oc:directiveContent "All competitor metrics must be from the same fiscal year with exceptions flagged explicitly. Convert to USD for international companies noting exchange rate and date. Missing data shows as '-' or 'N/A' with '[E]' for estimates — never blank. Every number needs a citation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Inconsistent or uncited data undermines the credibility of the entire competitive analysis." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_3d1c6c92 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Phase 1 scoping" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never guess scope — use ask_user_question to pin down scope, competitor set, audience depth, and investment context before any research or slide-building." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A 20-slide peer benchmarking deck and a 5-slide market map are both 'competitive analysis' and take completely different shapes." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_756da83c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building strategic context and investment scenario slides" ;
    oc:directiveContent """M&A Transaction: | Acquirer | Target | Date | Deal Value | Multiple | Rationale |
Scenario Analysis: | Scenario | Probability | Valuation | Key Assumptions |""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Acquirer",
        "Date",
        "Deal Value",
        "Key Assumptions",
        "Multiple",
        "Probability",
        "Rationale",
        "Scenario",
        "Target",
        "Valuation" .

oc:kn_7856cc98 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When sources provide conflicting data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Source hierarchy when data conflicts: 1) 10-Ks/annual reports, 2) Earnings calls/investor presentations, 3) Sell-side research, 4) Industry reports, 5) News (verify against primary)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Using higher-quality sources ensures data credibility and auditability of the competitive analysis." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_95cc1d78 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Quality checklist before final delivery" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before finishing: verify slide titles match user specs verbatim, charts appear where requested, all listed competitors/years/data points are present, every number has a citation, no overlapping elements, titles fit without overflow, and charts are real chart objects." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systematic verification catches the most common delivery defects that cause rework rounds." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a9a5016e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the complete deck" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Competitive analysis deck structure: Market Context → Industry Economics → Target Profile → Competitor Mapping → Positioning Visual → Competitor Deep-Dives (metrics table + qualitative table each) → Comparative Analysis (dimension × company matrix with ●●● ratings) → Strategic Context (M&A, partnerships) → Synthesis (moat assessment + bull/base/bear if investment context)" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Comparative Analysis",
        "Competitor Deep-Dives",
        "Competitor Mapping",
        "Industry Economics",
        "Market Context",
        "Positioning Visual",
        "Strategic Context",
        "Synthesis",
        "Target Profile" .

oc:kn_b3495674 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Step 0 — before any competitor analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Identify 3-5 industry-defining metrics before starting analysis and use them consistently across every competitor (e.g., SaaS: ARR, NRR, CAC payback, LTV/CAC, Rule of 40)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Industry-standard metrics provide the consistent frame needed for meaningful cross-competitor comparison." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c8837d9b a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before Phase 2 slide building" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never create slides until the outline is approved by the user. Propose slide titles with one-line content notes and get explicit confirmation first." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A competitive deck is 10-20 slides of interlocking content — rebuilding because an early slide was wrong is expensive. The outline is the cheap iteration point." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_dd021a32 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Scope analysis (scope, competitor set, audience, investment context) → 2. Propose outline, get approval → 3. Identify industry metrics → 4. Build market context slide → 5. Map industry economics → 6. Profile target company → 7. Map competitors by grouping lens → 8. Create positioning visualization → 9. Deep-dive each competitor → 10. Build comparative analysis → 11. Add strategic context → 12. Synthesize with moat assessment → 13. Run quality checklist" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_df718a12 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a target company profile slide" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Target Company Profile:
| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Revenue | $4.96B |
| Growth | +26% YoY |
| Gross Margin | 45% |
| Profitability | $373M Adj. EBITDA |
| Customers | 134K |
| Retention | 92% |
| Market Share | ~15% |""" .

oc:kn_f1d4507b a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Throughout all slide building" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When the user specifies slide titles, chart types, data series, or exact values, treat them as hard requirements — not suggestions. Use exact wording, exact formats, include every data point listed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Prompt fidelity prevents the most common source of rework — mismatched expectations between what the user asked for and what was delivered." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_f764c27d a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "All slide content creation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Slide titles must state insights not labels (e.g., 'Scale leaders pulling away from niche players' not 'Competitive Analysis'). Signposts must be quantified. Ratings must show actual values alongside symbols." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Insight-driven titles communicate the 'so what' immediately; topic labels require the reader to do the synthesis themselves." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

